The normalized wavelength dependence of the 2PA cross sections is in good agreement with the linear absorption spectrum in the wavelength range of 560–675 nm (Fig. 3b). Under 800–940 nm excitation, the 2PA cross section of the CDs increases as the wavelength decreases owing to the increase in the electronic density of states within the conduction band[62]. The maximum 2PA cross section (30160 GM (3.02 × 10−46cm4·s·photon−1)) peaks at around ∼ 1256 nm, which is considerably higher than those of nanographene, nanographene ribbons, and polymer CDs[63,64]. Table S3 compares the NLA coefficient (
α
NL
) and 2PA cross section (
σ 2
) of the RCDs derived in this work with those obtained in previous reports.
